{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":801,"text":"There have been many revolutions\nover the last century,"},{"time":4197,"text":"but perhaps none as significant\nas the longevity revolution."},{"time":9242,"text":"We are living on average\ntoday 34 years longer"},{"time":13616,"text":"than our great-grandparents did --\nthink about that."},{"time":16118,"text":"That's an entire second adult lifetime"},{"time":19396,"text":"that's been added to our lifespan."},{"time":21734,"text":"And yet, for the most part,"},{"time":23105,"text":"our culture has not come to terms\nwith what this means."},{"time":26500,"text":"We're still living with the old paradigm"},{"time":29289,"text":"of age as an arch."},{"time":31290,"text":"That's the metaphor, the old metaphor."},{"time":33230,"text":"You're born, you peak at midlife"},{"time":35364,"text":"and decline into decrepitude."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37500,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":39197,"text":"Age as pathology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42204,"text":"But many people today -- philosophers,\nartists, doctors, scientists --"},{"time":46500,"text":"are taking a new look\nat what I call \"the third act\" --"},{"time":49848,"text":"the last three decades of life."},{"time":52364,"text":"They realize that this is actually\na developmental stage of life"},{"time":57500,"text":"with its own significance,"},{"time":59914,"text":"as different from midlife\nas adolescence is from childhood."},{"time":65732,"text":"And they are asking --\nwe should all be asking:"},{"time":69109,"text":"How do we use this time?"},{"time":71684,"text":"How do we live it successfully?"},{"time":73636,"text":"What is the appropriate\nnew metaphor for aging?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":77594,"text":"I've spent the last year researching\nand writing about this subject."},{"time":81229,"text":"And I have come to find\nthat a more appropriate metaphor for aging"},{"time":86500,"text":"is a staircase --"},{"time":89071,"text":"the upward ascension of the human spirit,"},{"time":92182,"text":"bringing us into wisdom,\nwholeness, and authenticity."},{"time":96500,"text":"Age not at all as pathology."},{"time":98833,"text":"Age as potential."},{"time":100500,"text":"And guess what?"},{"time":101943,"text":"This potential is not for the lucky few."},{"time":104607,"text":"It turns out, most people over 50"},{"time":108700,"text":"feel better, are less stressed,\nless hostile, less anxious."},{"time":113011,"text":"We tend to see commonalities\nmore than differences."},{"time":116501,"text":"Some of the studies even say\nwe're happier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119335,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":120389,"text":"This is not what I expected, trust me."},{"time":123133,"text":"I come from a long line of depressives."},{"time":125928,"text":"As I was approaching my late 40s,"},{"time":128272,"text":"when I would wake up in the morning,"},{"time":130089,"text":"my first six thoughts\nwould all be negative."},{"time":132544,"text":"And I got scared."},{"time":133730,"text":"I thought, \"Oh my gosh.\nI'm going to become a crotchety old lady.\""},{"time":137500,"text":"But now that I am actually smack-dab\nin the middle of my own third act,"},{"time":142065,"text":"I realize I've never been happier."},{"time":145142,"text":"I have such a powerful\nfeeling of well-being."},{"time":149524,"text":"And I've discovered"},{"time":151376,"text":"that when you're inside oldness,"},{"time":153377,"text":"as opposed to looking\nat it from the outside,"},{"time":155754,"text":"fear subsides."},{"time":157048,"text":"You realize you're still yourself --"},{"time":159404,"text":"maybe even more so."},{"time":161270,"text":"Picasso once said, \"It takes\na long time to become young.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":165514,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":167706,"text":"I don't want to romanticize aging."},{"time":169580,"text":"Obviously, there's no guarantee"},{"time":171279,"text":"that it can be a time\nof fruition and growth."},{"time":174421,"text":"Some of it is a matter of luck."},{"time":176105,"text":"Some of it, obviously, is genetic."},{"time":178669,"text":"One third of it, in fact, is genetic."},{"time":180817,"text":"And there isn't much we can do about that."},{"time":183555,"text":"But that means that two-thirds\nof how well we do in the third act,"},{"time":188474,"text":"we can do something about."},{"time":190981,"text":"We're going to discuss what we can do"},{"time":193271,"text":"to make these added years\nreally successful,"},{"time":196698,"text":"and use them to make a difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199848,"text":"Now, let me say something\nabout the staircase,"},{"time":202064,"text":"which may seem like an odd\nmetaphor for seniors,"},{"time":206105,"text":"given the fact that many seniors\nare challenged by stairs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209092,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":210430,"text":"Myself included."},{"time":213888,"text":"As you may know, the entire world\noperates on a universal law:"},{"time":219143,"text":"entropy, the second law of thermodynamics."},{"time":222674,"text":"Entropy means that everything\nin the world -- everything --"},{"time":225587,"text":"is in a state of decline and decay --"},{"time":227773,"text":"the arch."},{"time":229389,"text":"There's only one exception\nto this universal law,"},{"time":233188,"text":"and that is the human spirit,"},{"time":235380,"text":"which can continue to evolve\nupwards, the staircase,"},{"time":239476,"text":"bringing us into wholeness,\nauthenticity, and wisdom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244404,"text":"And here's an example of what I mean."},{"time":246919,"text":"This upward ascension"},{"time":249000,"text":"can happen even in the face\nof extreme physical challenges."},{"time":252559,"text":"About three years ago,\nI read an article in the New York Times."},{"time":256872,"text":"It was about a man named Neil Selinger --"},{"time":258936,"text":"57 years old, a retired lawyer,"},{"time":261638,"text":"who had joined the writers'\ngroup at Sarah Lawrence,"},{"time":264737,"text":"where he found his writer's voice."},{"time":267576,"text":"Two years later,"},{"time":268817,"text":"he was diagnosed with ALS,\ncommonly known as Lou Gehrig's disease."},{"time":273167,"text":"It's a terrible disease. It's fatal."},{"time":275554,"text":"It wastes the body,\nbut the mind remains intact."},{"time":279627,"text":"In this article,\nMr. Selinger wrote the following"},{"time":283000,"text":"to describe what was happening to him."},{"time":286269,"text":"And I quote:"},{"time":288372,"text":"\"As my muscles weakened,"},{"time":291000,"text":"my writing became stronger."},{"time":293730,"text":"As I slowly lost my speech,"},{"time":296712,"text":"I gained my voice."},{"time":299206,"text":"As I diminished, I grew."},{"time":301880,"text":"As I lost so much,"},{"time":303741,"text":"I finally started to find myself.\""},{"time":308432,"text":"Neil Selinger, to me,"},{"time":309708,"text":"is the embodiment\nof mounting the staircase"},{"time":313113,"text":"in his third act."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315642,"text":"Now we're all born with spirit, all of us,"},{"time":318404,"text":"but sometimes it gets tamped down\nbeneath the challenges of life,"},{"time":322572,"text":"violence, abuse, neglect."},{"time":325507,"text":"Perhaps our parents\nsuffered from depression."},{"time":328111,"text":"Perhaps they weren't able to love us\nbeyond how we performed in the world."},{"time":333936,"text":"Perhaps we still suffer\nfrom a psychic pain, a wound."},{"time":338000,"text":"Perhaps we feel\nthat many of our relationships"},{"time":340589,"text":"have not had closure."},{"time":342000,"text":"And so we can feel unfinished."},{"time":345563,"text":"Perhaps the task of the third act"},{"time":349131,"text":"is to finish up the task\nof finishing ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353405,"text":"For me, it began as I was approaching\nmy third act, my 60th birthday."},{"time":359642,"text":"How was I supposed to live it?"},{"time":361563,"text":"What was I supposed to accomplish\nin this final act?"},{"time":364499,"text":"And I realized that,\nin order to know where I was going,"},{"time":368682,"text":"I had to know where I'd been."},{"time":370849,"text":"And so I went back\nand I studied my first two acts,"},{"time":375000,"text":"trying to see who I was then,"},{"time":377647,"text":"who I really was, not who my parents\nor other people told me I was,"},{"time":383114,"text":"or treated me like I was."},{"time":384764,"text":"But who was I?"},{"time":385956,"text":"Who were my parents --\nnot as parents, but as people?"},{"time":389753,"text":"Who were my grandparents?"},{"time":391482,"text":"How did they treat my parents?"},{"time":393272,"text":"These kinds of things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397305,"text":"I discovered, a couple of years later,"},{"time":399939,"text":"that this process that I had gone through"},{"time":402940,"text":"is called by psychologists\n\"doing a life review.\""},{"time":406704,"text":"And they say it can give new significance\nand clarity and meaning"},{"time":410594,"text":"to a person's life."},{"time":412690,"text":"You may discover, as I did,"},{"time":415386,"text":"that a lot of things\nthat you used to think were your fault,"},{"time":419326,"text":"a lot of things you used\nto think about yourself,"},{"time":422135,"text":"really had nothing to do with you."},{"time":425000,"text":"It wasn't your fault; you're just fine."},{"time":428280,"text":"And you're able to go back\nand forgive them."},{"time":432000,"text":"And forgive yourself."},{"time":433959,"text":"You're able to free yourself"},{"time":437146,"text":"from your past."},{"time":438912,"text":"You can work to change\nyour relationship to your past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443134,"text":"Now while I was writing about this,"},{"time":445061,"text":"I came upon a book called\n\"Man's Search for Meaning\""},{"time":448297,"text":"by Viktor Frankl."},{"time":449822,"text":"Viktor Frankl was a German psychiatrist"},{"time":452421,"text":"who'd spent five years\nin a Nazi concentration camp."},{"time":455722,"text":"And he wrote that,\nwhile he was in the camp,"},{"time":458674,"text":"he could tell, should\nthey ever be released,"},{"time":462151,"text":"which of the people would be OK,\nand which would not."},{"time":466960,"text":"And he wrote this:"},{"time":472115,"text":"\"Everything you have in life\ncan be taken from you"},{"time":474788,"text":"except one thing:"},{"time":476904,"text":"your freedom to choose\nhow you will respond to the situation."},{"time":483000,"text":"This is what determines\nthe quality of the life we've lived --"},{"time":486674,"text":"not whether we've been rich or poor,"},{"time":488754,"text":"famous or unknown,"},{"time":490510,"text":"healthy or suffering."},{"time":492714,"text":"What determines our quality of life\nis how we relate to these realities,"},{"time":498387,"text":"what kind of meaning we assign them,"},{"time":500563,"text":"what kind of attitude\nwe cling to about them,"},{"time":503754,"text":"what state of mind\nwe allow them to trigger.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":507746,"text":"Perhaps the central purpose\nof the third act"},{"time":510453,"text":"is to go back and to try, if appropriate,"},{"time":514454,"text":"to change our relationship to the past."},{"time":518714,"text":"It turns out that cognitive research shows"},{"time":521920,"text":"when we are able to do this,"},{"time":523724,"text":"it manifests neurologically --"},{"time":526327,"text":"neural pathways are created in the brain."},{"time":529444,"text":"You see, if you have, over time,"},{"time":531445,"text":"reacted negatively\nto past events and people,"},{"time":534872,"text":"neural pathways are laid down"},{"time":537178,"text":"by chemical and electrical signals\nthat are sent through the brain."},{"time":540976,"text":"And over time, these neural pathways\nbecome hardwired."},{"time":544470,"text":"They become the norm --\neven if it's bad for us,"},{"time":547320,"text":"because it causes us stress and anxiety."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550929,"text":"If, however,"},{"time":552413,"text":"we can go back and alter our relationship,"},{"time":556173,"text":"re-vision our relationship\nto past people and events,"},{"time":560493,"text":"neural pathways can change."},{"time":562466,"text":"And if we can maintain\nthe more positive feelings"},{"time":566448,"text":"about the past,"},{"time":567629,"text":"that becomes the new norm."},{"time":569455,"text":"It's like resetting a thermostat."},{"time":572872,"text":"It's not having experiences"},{"time":575960,"text":"that makes us wise."},{"time":579000,"text":"It's reflecting on the experiences\nthat we've had that makes us wise"},{"time":584293,"text":"and that helps us become whole,"},{"time":586294,"text":"brings wisdom and authenticity."},{"time":588531,"text":"It helps us become\nwhat we might have been."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592405,"text":"Women start off whole, don't we?"},{"time":594666,"text":"I mean, as girls, we're feisty --\n\"Yeah? Who says?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":597462,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":598536,"text":"We have agency."},{"time":599725,"text":"We are the subjects of our own lives."},{"time":602199,"text":"But very often,"},{"time":603607,"text":"many, if not most of us,\nwhen we hit puberty,"},{"time":606216,"text":"we start worrying\nabout fitting in and being popular."},{"time":609579,"text":"And we become the subjects\nand objects of other people's lives."},{"time":614000,"text":"But now, in our third acts,"},{"time":616770,"text":"it may be possible for us\nto circle back to where we started,"},{"time":622070,"text":"and know it for the first time."},{"time":624969,"text":"And if we can do that,"},{"time":626406,"text":"it will not just be for ourselves."},{"time":629618,"text":"Older women are the largest\ndemographic in the world."},{"time":633833,"text":"If we can go back and redefine ourselves"},{"time":637187,"text":"and become whole,"},{"time":638794,"text":"this will create\na cultural shift in the world,"},{"time":643548,"text":"and it will give an example\nto younger generations"},{"time":646793,"text":"so that they can reconceive\ntheir own lifespan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":649682,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650976,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}